{
  "doc_id": "4784",
  "text": "Populations of cells enriched for spermatogonia were prepared from P6 C57BL/6 mice using the StaPut method based on sedimentation velocity at unit gravity [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Briefly, testis cells (10 6 to 10 7 ) suspended in 2 ml of buffer plus 0.5% bovine serum albumin (BSA) were loaded onto a 50-ml gradient of 2%-4% BSA [CITATION_3] and allowed to sediment for 2.5 h at 48C. An aliquot of unfractionated cells (0.25 3 10 6 /ml) was also reserved as a control. Approximately one hundred 0.5-ml fractions were then collected in microcentrifuge tubes and analyzed for content of spermatogonia on the basis of morphology under phase contrast optics (which typically yields !85% purity). Fractions containing Sertoli cells or spermatogonia were pooled separately, concentrated (to 0.25 3 10 6 cells/ml), and stored in buffer containing fetal bovine serum (FBS) on ice until use.",
